The Gilded Rose Kata &ndash; Working with Legacy Code and Refactoring to Patterns &ndash;
Introduction About Coding Katas The Term &lsquo;Kata&rsquo; is a Metaphor taken from Martial Arts for a Pattern of Movements to Practice and Perfect those same Movements (Wikipedia:Kata). According to (Wikipedia:Kata), it was introduced as a practice to Software Craftsmanship by Dave Thomas in his blog, to practice developing software using techniques like TDD, Refactoring or the SOLID principles.
